                danced in the sunlight pouring through a narrow crack above. Shelves
                lined with strange books filled the walls, and at the center stood a
                brass pedestal holding a single open journal.
            </p>
            <p>
                Its pages were filled with sketches of unfamiliar maps and notes
                written in hurried, looping script—signed by someone named E.L. Marlowe.
            </p>
